asculinity; media coverage focusing, even today, on the novelty of a female candidate; public support for women that often evaporates in the voting booth; and more. Although Madam President is not an impossibility, they conclude, it would be a mistake to ignore the very significant hurdles that women still face on the path to the Oval Office.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Women in Politics.2bisacsh1 aBose, Meena, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aConroy, Meredith, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDuerst-Lahti, Georgia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFarrar-Myers, Victoria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFridkin, Kim L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGordon, Ann, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHan, Lori Cox, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeldman, Caroline, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aHeldman, Caroline, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHult, Karen M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchroedel, Jean Reith, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSerignese Woodall, Gina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aThomas, Sue, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertLynne Rienner Press Complete eBook-Package 2013-2000z978311078425140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978168585772140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781685857721423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781685857721/original  a978-3-11-078425-1 